    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-08T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T08:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-08T10:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 8, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>517. Department’s circular telegram December 7, 6 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">10
                        p.m.?</hi>] Oral communication regarding Japanese aggression has been
                    communicated to Guani<note n="63" xml:id="d138fn1">Alberto Guani, Uruguayan
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> who will give me the requested
                    expression of the views of the Uruguayan Government somewhat later. For the time
                    being he asked me to advise the Department that Uruguay considers itself already
                    solidly with the United States and is consulting other governments with a view
                    to making this solidarity effective throughout the continent. He mentioned in
                    particular consultation with Brazil and Argentina.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
